caption.text:
FOLLOW: @GameFacts 🎮

CONT’D: Via GameSpot “Our AI now has a new state of awareness between complete awareness of your position and totally unaware of where you are," The Last of Us Part II co-director Anthony Newman said in an interview with GameSpot. "We sometimes call that vague knowledge." For example, even if you were to stealthily take down an enemy with a silent weapon -such as a bow or pistol with a silencer attached to it--another enemy can still find the body, look at where the arrow or bullet is lodged in their comrade, and infer in which direction they were attacked. ℹ️

MY TAKE: Well that’s awesome. Looks like I have to buy the game now, although probably a good idea I complete the first one first. 🤗

QUESTION: What do you think of this news? Will you be buying it? 🤔

TAG: Any TLOU fans below. 🏷

caption.text:
Flicka da wrist by the Golden God himself | Steelwing plays Rainbow 6
.
.
.
.
.
#gaming #indiangamer #rainbow6 #headshots

Here is a list of everything I found out about the new season. * Gold backpack now grants extra shield and health to team mates upon ressing them.
* Gold body shield now has the old gold backpacks passive granting faster healing.
* While inside Gibby shield you gain a similar passive to Lifeline, meaning faster healing while inside the dome. The dome can also be thrown farther.
* Pathfinder's grapple is nerfed. From what I understand, it takes a second before you can be moved by the grapple instead of it instantly moving you.
* R301 and Flatline hop up that allows more damage while using single fire mode.
* EVA8 and G7 hop up that makes the gun shoot twice per trigger pull.
* Disruptor rounds and skull piercer have been removed.
* Wingman headshot damage up to compensate for skull piercer removal.
* There are new "futuristic" flyers that seem to change color (blue, purple, gold) on a time interval, and when destroyed will drop random loot that corresponds to the color when it was destroyed.
* New charge rifle is NOT a care package weapon.
* Longbow RoF nerf.
* Apparently the kill leader flags/banner things can show you how many enemies are in your area while viewing them in Crypto's drone.

.
رهيييبة الفكرة!😃.
.
.
المساعد الرقمي “Google Assistant” تستفيد منه العديد من الأجهزة كميزة رائعة فيها ولا سيما الهواتف الذكيّة وخصوصًا سلسلة هواتف Pixel ، ولكن وش ممكن يصير لو تطوّرت الفكرة وصارت حتى لأجهزة الألعاب مساعد رقمي ذكي؟🤔. سوني "سجّلت" براءة إختراع جديدة لمساعد ذكي داخل جهاز PS5 ، ولكن في الحقيقة @microsoft "أضافت" مساعد “Google Assistant” ضمن خدمات جهازها الأسطوري XBOX ONE عبر تحديث جديد بنسخة البيتا وصل لبعض مستخدمي الجهاز باللغة الإنكليزيّة البريطانيّة وقريبًا لبقيّة اللغات ولبقيّة الدول خلال خريف عام 2019👍🏻. وطبعًا الفائدة من مساعد جوجل ذا هو أنّك تقدر تعطيه أوامر بأنّه يقفّل تطبيق معيّن/يخرج القرص/يرفع ويخفض مستوى الصوت/يلتقط لقطة شاشة وغيرها الكثيير من المميّزات.
.
.
—
وش رأيكم بفكرة وجود مساعد ذكي مدمج داخل الجهاز لمساعدة اللاعبين وتسهيل تجربتهم؟ وهل تعتقدون بأن هذي الخاصيّة مطلوبة في أجهزة الجيل الجاي؟🤨.
—
.

Ontem um dos muitos spinoffs de Kingdom Hearts comemorou seu décimo aniversário de chegada as Américas. Em 29 de setembro de 2009, nosso lado do mundo recebeu Kingdom Hearts 358/2 Days para o Nintendo DS. Esse jogo que poucas pessoas sabem pronunciar o nome certo mostra a história de Roxas enquanto trabalhava para Organization XIII, com seus eventos ocorrendo entre o Kingdom Hearts e Kingdom Hearts 2, incluindo também Chain of Memories (outro spinoff que ainda não foi citado aqui). 358/2 Days é, na minha opinião, o que traz a história mais pesada e tapa vários buracos que haviam na trama. O jogo foi transformado em um filme com as cutscenes e está disponível nas coletâneas de PS3 e PS4. Para quem quiser jogar no DS, eu recomendo pela história, pois o gameplay é um pouco maçante.

Here are the finished trophies I made for Midas Mode! They feature Mr. Midas, the official mascot of the Dota 2 tournament hosted by Moonduck Studios. It’s no ordinary competition though. Instead of following the regular rules of Dota, there are bounties that players can earn in exchange for rewards. Here’s an example: “A math problem will be written in all chat between 5 and 10 minutes into each game. The first team that answers correctly will receive a reward.” It’s about as hilarious as it sounds and I’m ecstatic that I was able to be a part of it. Make sure to tune in to Twitch.tv/MoonduckTV this week and watch! I’ll be breaking down the details of how I made these guys, including the 3D printing, into separate posts~

أحتل فريق Bungie مكانة كبيرة وسط إستديوهات تطوير الفيديو جيم على مستوى العالم وذلك بعمله سابقاً على سلسلة ألعاب Halo الشهيرة قبل أن يقوم بالإنفصال عن شركة مايكروسوفت ويتعاون من جديد مع شركة Activision ليقدم معهم سلسلة Destiny التي حصلت على شهرة واسعة أيضاً وأحتلت مكانة كبيرة مع ألعاب منظور الشخص الأول الأخرى ، الفريق قام مؤخراً بالإنفصال أيضاً عن شركة Activision وهو يطمح لأن يصبح واحد من أشهر فرق تطوير الفيديو جيم المستقلة على مستوى العالم ومن خلال مقابلة مع موقع IGN صرح المدير التنفيذي للفريق السيد (Pete Parsons) ” بجانب سلسلة Destiny يعمل الفريق على عنوان جديد تماماً سيكون هذا العنوان جاهز للإصدار قبل عام 2025 على أقصى تقدير ” وأضاف أيضاً ” العنوان الجديد هو تحت التطوير في الوقت الحالي ونريد بتطويره أن يصبح الفريق واحد من الإستديوهات التي لها بصمة واضحة في الصناعة على مستوى العالم ” . .

This is a real photo of Bruce McCandless floating untethered in space.⠀In this Feb. 7, 1984 photograph taken by his fellow crewmembers aboard the Earth-orbiting Space Shuttle Challenger on the STS-41B mission, NASA astronaut Bruce McCandless II approaches his maximum distance from the vehicle. McCandless became the first astronaut to maneuver about in space untethered, during this first "field" tryout of a nitrogen-propelled, hand-controlled backpack device called the Manned Maneuvering Unit (MMU).⠀For 50 years, NASA has been "suiting up" for spacewalking. The first American to conduct a spacewalk, astronaut Edward H. White II, floated into the vastness of space on the Gemini IV mission on June 3, 1965. For more than 20 minutes, White maneuvered himself around the Gemini spacecraft as it traveled from over Hawaii to the Gulf of Mexico--making his orbital stroll 6,500 miles long. At the end of the 20-minute spacewalk, White was exuberant. "This is the greatest experience," he said. "It's just tremendous."⠀Since this historic first, NASA astronauts have performed spacewalks, or extravehicular activity (EVA) in NASA-speak, on the Gemini, Apollo, Skylab, Space Shuttle and International Space Station programs. Astronauts have explored the lunar surface, completed 82 spacewalks outside of the space shuttle, and 187 spacewalks, to date, outside the International Space Station. A total of 166 hours of spacewalks were carried out to service the Hubble Space Telescope. Today, NASA is developing new advanced spacesuits for use by astronauts as they travel to new deep-space locations on the journey to Mars. The next-generation suit will incorporate a number of technology advances to shorten preparation time, improve safety and boost astronaut capabilities during spacewalks and surface activities.⠀Via NASA#universe_dop #toptorontotech #technology #tech2019 #technews #shotoniphone #huaweip30pro #huaweicanada #pixel4 #techreviews #science #tech #Toronto #space #STEM #computers #gaming #gamers  CREDIT: @universe_dope@TopTechToronto: Your Tech 🔌 ——————————————————— ⁣
